rubric.description:
Students will submit  HTML and CSS files for a web page that only requires the use of basic knowledge of HTML and CSS. 

Here's [one example](http://codepen.io/AndyAtUdacity/full/PwKdry/) of what students could make and here is [the code](http://codepen.io/AndyAtUdacity/pen/PwKdry?editors=110) that goes along with it.

### Student Instructions: 
In this project, you'll use both HTML and CSS to make a professional-looking web page! Be sure to look through the notes you've taken to make sure you understand the fundamental HTML and CSS concepts you've learned throughout the course so far. 

And remember, you can make this project on *any* topic you'd like!

### Code Review
Your reviewer will look at the code you've written and provide feedback on each rubric item for the project. You can view the rubric [here](https://review.udacity.com/#!/projects/3836128891/rubric).

* **Use of Syntax**: All of your HTML and CSS should be properly formatted and should pass [HTML validation](http://validator.w3.org/) and [CSS validation](https://jigsaw.w3.org/css-validator/) tests. 

We recommend that you look over the [project rubric](https://review.udacity.com/#!/projects/3836128891/rubric) to make sure your project meets requirements before submitting your project.

If you are feeling stuck on the project, please check out the discussions on our [student forums](https://forums.udacity.com). Or consider [scheduling an appointment](https://calendly.com/ipnd-1-1) with one of our mentors.
